<item>
            <title>[FELIX-6132] XSS possible in service console</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/FELIX-6132</link>
                <project id="12310100" key="FELIX">Felix</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;Issue Summary :&lt;/b&gt;&#160;There is a&#160;XSS possible in system console.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;Steps to reproduce :&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ol&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Open a local instance&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Open the link&#160;&lt;a href=&quot;http://localhost:4502/system/console/services?filter=%22onmouseover=%22alert(%27xss%27)%22&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://localhost:4502/system/console/services?filter=%22onmouseover=%22alert(%27xss%27)%22&lt;/a&gt;&#160;in Internet Explorer. A pop would come when you mouse over the filter input box.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Chrome would auto flag XSS exploit and prevent page load&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;


&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;Expected Behavior :&lt;/b&gt;&#160;The pop up should not come up.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
